            <Title>了解你自己并理解你的动机Know yourself and understand your motivations</Title>
            <Text>作为重点投资者，关键在于了解自己与投资相关的气质。 如果您的一只股票的价格下跌了50％，但其内在价值并没有改变，您是否能够在不急于出售头寸的情况下处理这种损失？ 您是否容易受到您的朋友或媒体“专家”对您的投资的评论？ 当他们称你为傻子没有拥有当前热门股票时，你能处理好朋友的低调吗？
花费时间来发现你的心理倾向和动机 - 什么“推动你的按钮” - 所以你在做出未来的决定时可以考虑到这些。 太多投资者真的不知道是什么推动了他们的选择; 他们往往会回避它“恰到好处”的理由。当您阅读本章时，问问自己在您的投资决策过程中是否存在以下任何因素。
As a focus investor, it’s essential that you understand your own temperament as it relates to investing. If the price of one of your stocks drops by 50%, but its intrinsic value hasn’t changed, will you be able to handle that loss without rushing to sell the position? Are you easily influenced by what your friends or the media “experts” say about your investments? Will you be able to deal with the condescension of your friends when they call you a fool for not owning the current hot stock?
It will be worth the time spent to discover your psychological tendencies and motivations—what “pushes your buttons”—so you can take these into account when making future decisions. Too many investors really don’t know what drives their choices; they often fall back on the reasoning that it “just feels right.” As you read through this chapter, ask yourself if any of the following factors play a role in your investment decision-making process.</Text>
