            <Title>Incentives</Title>
            <Text>Many of the theories that economists use are based on another theory—that people make decisions and take advantage of incentives in a rational manner. Clearly, however, this is not always the case! In making investment decisions we must understand how a management team is compensated, as that can influence the team’s investment preferences. If a board of directors gives its management team a larger block of stock options, will members of management then be influenced to take more risks in their investments in the business, hoping the options will gain in value? They generally won’t admit it, but these types of incentives profoundly affect the decisions they make.
The book Freakonomics offers an excellent example, involving real estate agents, of just how influential incentives can be. Conventional wisdom suggests that, because real estate agents work on commission, they would try to obtain the highest possible selling price on your home (first-level thinking). The authors discovered a different reality, however: Real estate agents keep their own homes on the market far longer than their clients and sell them for higher prices! To understand why, all you need to do is look at their incentives. The percentage difference in the commission the agents receive by getting a higher closing price for their clients is not enough to justify the extra time and energy it takes to achieve that higher price. Of course, when their own house sells, they earn the entire difference!

经济学家使用的许多理论都是基于另一种理论 - 人们以理性的方式做出决策并利用激励机制。显然，但情况并非总是如此！在做出投资决策时，我们必须了解管理团队如何得到补偿，因为这会影响团队的投资偏好。如果董事会给管理团队更多的股票期权，那么管理层成员是否会受到影响，在其业务投资中承担更多的风险，希望期权可以获得价值？他们通常不会承认，但是这些激励措施深刻地影响了他们做出的决定。
“魔法经济学”这本书提供了一个很好的例子，涉及房地产经纪人，如何有影响力的激励措施。传统的观点认为，由于房地产经纪人是从事佣金工作的，所以他们会试图在家庭中获得尽可能高的销售价格（一级思维）。然而，作者发现了一个不同的现实：房地产经纪人在市场上保留自己的房屋的时间远远长于他们的客户，并以更高的价格出售。要理解为什么，你所要做的就是看看他们的激励。代理商通过为客户获得更高的收盘价而获得的佣金的百分比差异不足以证明实现更高价格需要额外的时间和精力。当然，当他们自己的房子卖，他们赚取全部的差异！</Text>
