            <Title>寡头垄断Oligopoly</Title>
            <Text>Oligopolies consist of several firms in the same market that compete on features other than price. Price wars, in which all the market players slash prices, tend toward lower profits for all the firms, leaving the market share of each company largely unchanged. Instead, oligopolistic firms tend to compete, through advertising, for product or service quality. Companies that form the oligopoly are generally safe from new companies entering the market because the barriers to entry are high.
寡头垄断由同一市场上的几家公司组成，这些公司在价格之外竞争。 所有市场参与者大幅度降价的价格战往往会导致所有企业的利润下降，使得每家企业的市场份额基本保持不变。 相反，寡头企业倾向于通过广告来竞争产品或服务质量。 形成寡头垄断的企业通常是安全的，因为新进入市场的门槛很高。</Text>
